Azure resources within a VNet can communicate with each other using private IP addresses.

This internal communication is secure and does not traverse the public internet.

For example, a web server can communicate with a database server within the same VNet.

A real-life use case is a multi-tier application where frontend, backend, and database interact internally.

Another example is microservices architecture where services communicate securely within a VNet.

This internal communication ensures performance, security, and low latency.
